        "text_tkV8Wc": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Grease and fats naturally rise and stick to the top and sides of your drain lines, while sugars and starches sink and build up at the bottom, eventually leading to blockages. This creates foul odors, attracts drain flies, requires frequent grease trap or interceptor maintenance, and often results in clogged leach fields. In severe cases, the buildup contributes to pollution and can lead to costly fines and wastewater surcharges.</p><p>By using <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/products/grease-blast?variant=43578945536034\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/products/drip-injection-system\"><strong>Environmental Biotech’s live vegetative bacteria</strong></a>, you can prevent these issues entirely—eliminating drain line blockages, reducing odors, and avoiding expensive equipment repairs and downtime for your facility.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
